# Animation Patterns

## Framer Motion Setup

Import from `"framer-motion"`. Use `motion.*` components for animated elements.

## Always Respect prefers-reduced-motion

```tsx
import { useReducedMotion } from "framer-motion"

function AnimatedComponent() {
  const prefersReduced = useReducedMotion()

  return (
    <motion.div
      animate={prefersReduced ? {} : { opacity: [0.4, 1, 0.4] }}
      transition={prefersReduced ? {} : { duration: 3, repeat: Infinity }}
    />
  )
}
```

Or use CSS media query for purely CSS animations:
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .animated { animation: none; }
}
```

## Campfire Motion Principles

The site has a **slow, warm, breathing** ambient motion language — not snappy or bouncy.

| Use case | Duration | Easing |
|---|---|---|
| Page transitions | 0.4–0.6s | `easeInOut` |
| Element reveals (scroll) | 0.5–0.8s | `easeOut` |
| Ambient loops (sparks, glow) | 2–4s | `easeInOut`, repeat `Infinity` |
| Hover states | 0.15–0.2s | `easeOut` |
| UX toggle transition | 0.3s | `easeInOut` |

## Scroll Reveal Pattern

```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 16 }}
  whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-10%" }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.6, ease: "easeOut" }}
/>
```

## Ambient Loop Pattern (sparks, glow)

```tsx
<motion.div
  animate={{ opacity: [0.3, 0.8, 0.3], scale: [1, 1.05, 1] }}
  transition={{ duration: 3, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" }}
/>
```

## GPU Compositing

Prefer animating `opacity`, `transform` (translate, scale, rotate) — these use GPU compositing.
Avoid animating `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `background-color` — these trigger layout/paint.
